# Obsidian Bases

Create and manage .base files for structured views of Obsidian notes.

## File Format

`.base` files are JSON with this structure:

```json
{
  "name": "My Base",
  "source": "folder:Projects",
  "columns": [
    { "id": "name", "type": "text", "name": "Name" },
    { "id": "status", "type": "select", "name": "Status",
      "options": ["active", "done", "blocked"] },
    { "id": "priority", "type": "number", "name": "Priority" },
    { "id": "due", "type": "date", "name": "Due Date" }
  ],
  "filters": [],
  "sorts": [{ "column": "priority", "direction": "desc" }],
  "view": "table"
}
```

## Source Types

| Source | Syntax | Notes |
|--------|--------|-------|
| Folder | `"folder:Projects"` | All notes in folder |
| Tag | `"tag:#project"` | All notes with tag |
| Link | `"link:[[Hub Note]]"` | Notes linked from a note |
| Query | `"query:status = active"` | Dataview-style query |

## Column Types

| Type | Values | Notes |
|------|--------|-------|
| `text` | String | Default for unknown fields |
| `number` | Integer or float | Supports formulas |
| `date` | ISO date string | `YYYY-MM-DD` format |
| `select` | Single value from options | Define `options` array |
| `multiselect` | Multiple values | Array of strings |
| `checkbox` | true/false | Renders as checkbox |
| `link` | `[[note name]]` | Obsidian wikilink |

## Filter Syntax

```json
{
  "filters": [
    { "column": "status", "operator": "eq", "value": "active" },
    { "column": "priority", "operator": "gte", "value": 3 },
    { "column": "due", "operator": "before", "value": "today" }
  ]
}
```

| Operator | For types | Meaning |
|----------|-----------|---------|
| `eq` / `neq` | All | Equal / not equal |
| `gt` / `gte` / `lt` / `lte` | number, date | Comparison |
| `contains` | text, multiselect | Substring or includes |
| `empty` / `notEmpty` | All | Field presence |
| `before` / `after` | date | Date comparison |

## View Types

| View | Best for |
|------|----------|
| `table` | Structured data, sortable columns |
| `board` | Kanban-style, grouped by a select column |
| `calendar` | Time-based, grouped by date column |
| `gallery` | Visual cards with images |
| `list` | Simple list view |

## Anti-Examples

| Bad | Why | Better |
|-----|-----|--------|
| Editing .base files as markdown | They're JSON, markdown edits break them | Edit as JSON or use Obsidian UI |
| Huge filters with 10+ conditions | Slow, hard to debug | Split into multiple bases |
| Not defining column types | Default text type loses sorting/filtering | Explicit types for every column |
